<p>Though we did a little Lindy Hopping beforehand, we were all business when riding <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?hl=en&amp;doflg=ptm&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;msa=0&amp;msid=100713211184899290190.000477a944849ec7f4d2e&amp;ll=40.035501,-105.30241&amp;spn=0.083328,0.136471&amp;t=p&amp;z=13">Linden Loop</a> for the first time in a while today.</p>
<p>Dave crunched the numbers and deemed the ride "safe" for a coumadin patient&mdash;I think he uses an old Russian calculator.  I'd have to say, he's looking pretty healthy to me.</p>
<p>Mr. U flew up Linden like a <a href="http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/09082007/58/kashechkin-positive-rocks-astana.html">Kazakh on Team Astana</a>, making it tough for drug-free Matt to latch on.  </p>